parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause the wipers to become inoperative, reducing visibility during rain or snow, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Windshield wipers work intermittently
wipers do not respond when turned on
wipers become inoperative while in use
wipers fail to turn back on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat frame can cause the seat to move from side to side, potentially leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Broken metal bolts on the seat
seat moves from side to side
feeling of something falling apart on the seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A loose seat runner or seat mounting failure can cause the seat to move unexpectedly, which can lead to loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially during sudden acceleration or deceleration.
symptoms: The seat moves or shifts while accelerating or decelerating
the seat pops or makes a loud noise
the seat bolt moves or becomes loose
the seat falls backwards into the rear seat during impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
